cs.IR, cs.SE, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper deals with the problem of searching a database of source codes, which can be seen as an information retrieval problem. 
2. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper is concerned with helping programmers complete their code, which is a software engineering problem. 
3. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper proposes a neural model for predicting which database code is likely to be most useful, which falls under the domain of natural language processing. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper casts contextualized code search as a learning problem and proposes a neural model for predicting the most useful code. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a machine learning approach for contextualized code search, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence.
